Sentencas: The cathode catalytic activity and stability in a temperature range of 550-700 degrees C is crucial to the development of proton-conductive solid oxide fuel cells (PCFCs).
Titulo: A dual modification strategy of highly active catalytic cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-doped PrBaFe 1.9 Mo 0.1 O 6-δ

Sentencas: A facile dual-modification strategy is developed for the design of Ni-doped PrBaFe1.9Mo0.1O6-delta (PBFMN), composed of a major perovskite and a minor NiO phases, as a cobaltfree cathode.
Titulo: A dual modification strategy of highly active catalytic cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-doped PrBaFe 1.9 Mo 0.1 O 6-δ

Sentencas: The composite cathode PBFMN exhibits high catalytic activity and stability.
Titulo: A dual modification strategy of highly active catalytic cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-doped PrBaFe 1.9 Mo 0.1 O 6-δ

Sentencas: Computational simulation indicates that the perovskite phase increases the oxygen vacancies and enhances the proton transfer, while nickel oxide nanoparticles improve oxygen adsorption and dissociation.
Titulo: A dual modification strategy of highly active catalytic cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-doped PrBaFe 1.9 Mo 0.1 O 6-δ

Sentencas: The fuel cell with as-prepared PBFMN reached a peak power density 1.23 W cm-2 at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: A dual modification strategy of highly active catalytic cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-doped PrBaFe 1.9 Mo 0.1 O 6-δ

Sentencas: The improved performance of the cell is mainly due to the fast ORR kinetics.
Titulo: A dual modification strategy of highly active catalytic cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-doped PrBaFe 1.9 Mo 0.1 O 6-δ

Sentencas: This work provides a new insight into the design of cobalt-free cathode for a PCFC.
Titulo: A dual modification strategy of highly active catalytic cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-doped PrBaFe 1.9 Mo 0.1 O 6-δ
